    },
    {
        "content": "<p>From the foreword (notes to the reader) of Lam's <em>Introduction to Quadratic Forms over Fields</em>:<br>\n<a href=\"/user_uploads/3121/CNXkW2MOyGmYyEcsrWQvNqtS/image.png\">image.png</a><br>\nI looked into the three references but didn't see char 2 global fields being treated.</p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/3121/CNXkW2MOyGmYyEcsrWQvNqtS/image.png\" title=\"image.png\"><img data-original-content-type=\"image/png\" data-original-dimensions=\"1216x363\" src=\"/user_uploads/thumbnail/3121/CNXkW2MOyGmYyEcsrWQvNqtS/image.png/840x560.webp\"></a></div><p>Cassels' book sketches a proof for number fields but not global function fields:<br>\n<a href=\"/user_uploads/3121/OFexZ7PIL3Ne22Hl8HVfnLbV/image.png\">image.png</a></p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/3121/OFexZ7PIL3Ne22Hl8HVfnLbV/image.png\" title=\"image.png\"><img data-original-content-type=\"image/png\" data-original-dimensions=\"700x850\" src=\"/user_uploads/thumbnail/3121/OFexZ7PIL3Ne22Hl8HVfnLbV/image.png/840x560.webp\"></a></div><p>Gerstein's <em>Basic Quadratic Forms</em> refers to O'Meara's <em>Introduction to Quadratic Forms</em> for a unified proof:<br>\n<a href=\"/user_uploads/3121/zRxxV-e4CxNOwcBtfAWWk4zI/image.png\">image.png</a><br>\n<a href=\"/user_uploads/3121/28LTLmDDwZbHP2bI9mvmRtI_/image.png\">image.png</a></p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/3121/zRxxV-e4CxNOwcBtfAWWk4zI/image.png\" title=\"image.png\"><img data-original-content-type=\"image/png\" data-original-dimensions=\"927x715\" src=\"/user_uploads/thumbnail/3121/zRxxV-e4CxNOwcBtfAWWk4zI/image.png/840x560.webp\"></a></div><div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/3121/28LTLmDDwZbHP2bI9mvmRtI_/image.png\" title=\"image.png\"><img data-original-content-type=\"image/png\" data-original-dimensions=\"1059x706\" src=\"/user_uploads/thumbnail/3121/28LTLmDDwZbHP2bI9mvmRtI_/image.png/840x560.webp\"></a></div>",
